race.comment: BIG TIGER (1) raced wide without cover but refused to lie down on debut last start over 1300m at Warwick Farm, eventually beaten just 0.4 lengths into third. Ideally placed over a slightly longer trip and with even luck in running should be right in the finish. RIEZ SOUVENT (5) debuted in the same race as BIG TIGER and was safely held. Settled just off the pace that day and couldn't quicken but wasn't too far away. Worth another chance over the extra 100m. WAR KING (6) copped early interference and raced fiercely so his effort to finish third when resuming over 1200m at Kembla was full of merit. Check the performance of Pimlico in Race 1 today, the winner of that Kembla maiden. MISS LOLA (9) has hit the line well to fill minor placings in her two runs this prep, both over shorter journeys at Warwick Farm. Blinkers on and stepping up in trip. Looms as a serious threat. IRON LEGEND (8) went okay on debut at Newcastle although this is a far tougher assignment.
